            <thetext>..., one for the browser app, one for the demos. This has since long bothered 
me, and I wanted the separation of the two invocations such that the actual 
*compile* would be done in one.

In general, the use of two generator processes is necessary, as the config file 
for the demos is generated dynamically, so it is not available when the main 
config file is being processes. So far, the border line has been drawn after 
the browser app has been generated. Then, a separate generator process was 
started to compile the demos. This impedes analysing and optimizing in some 
cases.</thetext>
